value.string:
DECLARE @CurrentWeekEndingDate DATE

SELECT TOP 1 @CurrentWeekEndingDate =
WeekEndingDate
FROM Dimensions.NRFWeeks
WHERE WeekEndingDate < GETDATE()
ORDER BY WeekEndingDate DESC

SELECT
REPLACE(CustYearWeek, '-', '') YearWeek
FROM Dimensions.CustomerWeeks
WHERE SoldTo = '0000105212'
AND WeekEndingDate = @CurrentWeekEndingDate
Getting current year week from SQL database
